main event: An unidentified flying object was reported observed during a lunar eclipse on 18 December 1964 in Cudahy, Wisconsin.
interesting points: The report mentions that no objects were observed but conflicting data made it unreliable., The observation lasted for approximately 7 seconds., The object reportedly moved from the northeast to the south., Analysts concluded that there was no definitive conclusion on the reported sighting., The report was part of the Project Blue Book investigation.
witness description: A civilian reported observing a strange ascending object in the sky at night, describing it as dark and airplane-like, changing in speed, brightness, and color.
